# UI Standards

## Theme

- Background: `#0a0a0a` (near-black)
- Accent: amber/gold — `#f59e0b` / Tailwind `amber-500`
- Use one accent color consistently; do not introduce new brand colors
- Text hierarchy: white for headings, `gray-400` for secondary text

## Component Rules

- Functional components only — no class components
- Use Tailwind utility classes for all styling
- No inline `style=` props
- No separate `.css` files beyond `app/globals.css`
- Mobile-first layout — stack below `768px` using `md:` breakpoints

## States

Every interactive component must handle four states:

| State   | Behaviour                                  |
|---------|--------------------------------------------|
| idle    | Default, waiting for user action           |
| loading | Spinner or skeleton, inputs disabled       |
| ready   | Data available, user can act               |
| active  | Recording, playing audio, speaking         |

Use Tailwind `transition` and `duration-` classes between state changes.

## Errors and Feedback

- Surface errors on screen — not just in the browser console
- Use a visible error message component, not an alert()
- Show loading indicators whenever an async operation is in progress

## How to Build UI

- Build components directly in Cursor using Tailwind to match the existing dark theme
- Match the look and feel of what's already in `components/` — do not redesign existing components unless asked
- If given a screenshot or description, build to match it without changing the theme or layout logic
- Do not introduce new UI libraries (e.g. shadcn, MUI, Chakra) without team agreement
